				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Hollowshade Wars - Unseating The Grimlings.<a name="28054"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 16 04 10:17 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I was really losing my patience last night - at level 53 I felt it would be more than reasonable to be able to solo the Hollowshade Wars.
<br />
I have slain the owlbear mother about 3 times now (no Flowing Thought drop yet... sigh) but in each instance that I've soloed the war, someone had unseated the Grimlings in the south and left either the wolves or owlbears in charge of that.
<br />
Once the zone is reset, I have been unable to unseat the Grimlings to restart the war.
<br />
(I know I don't have to START with the Grimlings, but I do have to unseat them at some point in time... and I'm stumped.)
<br />

<br />
From info I've gleaned from this site =) , I can kill the Grimling Chieftain IF I bring <a target="_new" href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=8634">Gamali</a> over to the Grimling camp, charm her, and send her in to do my dirty work.
<br />
Okay.  Chieftain dead.
<br />
Now I have tried both: a) zoning to clear aggro, releasing Gamali from my service, and b) attempting to keep Gamali charmed, and sending her in to attack one of the Grimling defenders that I have to defeat.
<br />
Either way, once the defenders start taking damage, I start taking adds - spiritists, bodyguards, priests, all highly offended at my intervention.
<br />
I get dispelled (bye Virtue! I hardly knew you!) and dotted, and soon the defender(s) start summoning me.
<br />
Okay - things aren't going well - time to RUN, a bard's iron clad defense!
<br />
Well, not this time: I run, run, run... ALMOST out of range....
<br />
(summon)
<br />
(damage)
<br />
Run, run, run, this time I'm gonna make it....
<br />
(summon)
<br />
(damage)
<br />
At which point I'm usually slain.
<br />

<br />
One time, I said &quot;to h*ll with THIS crap&quot;, and I decided to gate out, using my Worker's Sledgemallet (gates to Overthere), so I equip it, turn and start wailing on the swarm... health dropping, still not proccing... dropping, dropping, GATE!
<br />
Woot! <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />
Victory from the hands of defeat!
<br />
But no!  My weakened state aggros a nearby Overthere guard! Slash! Hack!
<br />
Dead. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-12.gif" border="0" alt="Mad" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
All right, enough of my horror stories.
<br />
How to deal with the Grimling Defenders.
<br />
I would welcome anyone's strategies and suggestions - these guys must die.
<br />
One idea I thought of was - kill chieftain, ignore the defenders for a while, and attempt to swarm kite all the possible adds out of commission FIRST, keeping a healthy MR twist up to keep from getting dotted too badly.
<br />
Then, once I've cleared most/all of the surrounding mobs, try tackling the defenders.
<br />
But I dunno.
<br />
Any advice would be great!
<br />
</span></td>
